definitions.definition: A standstill resulting from the opposition of two evenly matched forces ; a stalemate or impasse .
examples: The negotiation ended in deadlock , with neither party willing to compromise on the price.

definitions.definition: An inability to continue due to two programs or devices each requiring a response from the other before completing an operation .
Synonym of deadbolt ( “ type of lock ” ) .
